{"type":"message","id":"6049b395","parentId":"ffea5226","timestamp":"2026-04-09T14:35:30.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to fix all the issues identified in the self-check report. Let me review the high/medium/low priority items and start working on them one by one.\n\nLooking at the report, the priorities are:\n\n**High Priority:**\n1. System single point of failure risk - introduce backup mechanism or cloud server\n2. Backtest-live trading deviation - add out-of-sample validation, add slippage cost\n3. Extreme market response - create emergency procedures for limit up/down\n\n**Medium Priority:**\n4. Position concentration too high - introduce volatility-weighted position sizing\n5. Data cleaning process not standardized - add anomaly detection module\n6. Monitoring alert mechanism missing - introduce basic monitoring alerts\n7. Research documentation not systematically managed - establish Notion/Feishu doc library\n\n**Low Priority:**\n8. Fault review mechanism incomplete - create SOP + review form\n9. Knowledge accumulation insufficient - establish case library/factor library\n10. Historical data period insufficient - extend data storage period\n\nThis is a significant task. Let me start working through these methodically and create concrete fixes/improvements.\n\nFor each fix, I should:\n1. Understand the current state (if possible)\n2. Create/implement the fix\n3. Document what was done\n\nLet me start with the high priority items and work down. This will require creating scripts, configs, documentation, etc.\n\nGiven the scope, I should tackle these systematically. Let me start with creating fixes for each category.\n","thinkingSignature":"ceb16b38062d66d090d3a268aeeaeffe450055a36b94ce0cc21f6a1128441cf9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好的，我来逐一修复这些优先级问题。先从高优先级开始。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f0s7potffoeq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/codi